other_tests.findings: Lower chest shows bibasilar subsegmental atelectasis; otherwise, visualized lung fields are within normal limits. Abdominal organs including liver, pancreas, spleen, and adrenal glands are normal. Kidneys show several renal cysts but no suspicious lesions. There is a small hiatus hernia and small bowel loops diffusely distended but no bowel obstruction. Postoperative changes include suture material along the tip of the cecum and a small locule of free air. Small volume nonhemorrhagic free fluid in the pelvis.
